cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL. 

This paper is about improving the efficiency of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a learning algorithm, which suggests that it could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of a reward function and data-driven approach suggests it could also be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions experiments on semantic segmentation tasks, which could place it under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
